@Puzzled Brit

It might be a little dated, but it was certainly a thing when I played a little tennis about 40-50 years ago.  It's not likely something you'll hear on a broadcast; it's something rec players say when calling out the score.  When the server states the score, AD IN means "advantage me" and ad out means "advantage you."

In other words, you need to have played tennis, not just watched it.

